ds, pump the rear brake pedal slowly until the plate is held by the brake pads. Do not allow the pistons to fall out.","Remove the front caliper mounting fixings and slide the brake caliper off the brake disc.","Fixings","Caliper","Using a suitable flat metal plate approximately 2 mm thick and 30 to 50 mm wide (for example a gasket scraper) between the brake pads, pump the front brake lever slowly until the plate is held by the brake pads. Do not allow the pistons to fall out.","Remove the union bolts and carefully disconnect the four brake lines from the ABS modulator, collecting any brake fluid. Discard the sealing washers.","ABS modulator","Brake line unions","Remove and discard the two fixings and remove the ABS modulator from its bracket.","ABS modulator","ABS modulator bracket","Fixings","If necessary, release the fixing and remove the anti-rotation moulding from the ABS modulator.","ABS modulator","Fixing","Anti-rotation moulding"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType05","views":[],"createdAt":"2024-01-18T15:57:58.318Z","updatedAt":"2024-01-18T15:57:58.318Z","__v":0}